<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-17T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-17T06:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/1015: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-17T11:00:00+00:00">August 17, 1935—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 17—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>54. My telegram No. 53, August 14, 2 a.m. Sub-Minister says exchange
                                insurance experimental with four nations and probably will be
                                extended to all others if it works satisfactorily. Originated with
                                Ministry of Finance.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>